# Rasm C# Testing

Read `.claude/skills/testing-cs/SKILL.md`, `tests/csharp/AGENTS.md`, and nearest test `AGENTS.md`. File-specific rules own `*.spec.cs`, `_testkit`, and `*.verify.csx`.

## Rail split

| [INDEX] | [RAIL]                      |
| :-----: | --------------------------- |
|   [1]   | `rasm-csharp-specs.mdc`     |
|   [2]   | `rasm-testkit.mdc`          |
|   [3]   | `rasm-bridge-scenarios.mdc` |
|   [4]   | Architecture tests          |
|   [5]   | Benchmarks and fuzz         |

[OWNS]
- [1] Pure-managed xUnit/CsCheck behavior and law-matrix specs
- [2] Shared generators, oracles, adapters, and scenario capsules
- [3] Native Rhino/GH2 runtime paths
- [4] Assembly dependency direction only
- [5] Separate executables, not xUnit

## Shared Constraints

- Keep static, unit, runtime, benchmark, and fuzz rails independent.
- Keep architecture tests focused on dependency direction, not behavioral assertions.
- Keep benchmarks and fuzz harnesses outside normal xUnit execution.
- Never mirror current implementation output as an oracle.

## Validation ladder

Run `uv run python -m tools.quality static fix [paths...]` for changed C# test files when safe autofix is desired. Run `uv run python -m tools.quality static build [paths...]` when compile/analyzer proof is needed. Run `uv run python -m tools.quality test run --no-build` after a successful static build. Use `uv run python -m tools.quality test run --target <csproj>` for non-default projects. Run `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge verify <scenario-or-glob>` only for bridge-owned runtime behavior.
